<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-86DD4BDE-3D7B-4275-BC87-9A4583245A1B" version="2" lang="en-US"?><tsTroubleshooting xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-86DD4BDE-3D7B-4275-BC87-9A4583245A1B" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" domains="(topic tsTroubleshooting)                            (topic hi-d)    (topic sdlVariables-c)                             (topic ut-d)                             (topic indexing-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c tsTroubleshooting oceTroubleshooting-c)   " class="- topic/topic tsTroubleshooting/tsTroubleshooting "><title translate="no" class="- topic/title ">19713 Blouse forming device not lifted</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-B87BF88B-91B2-4C27-A55C-91B9B6986C8A"><p class="- topic/p ">Blouse forming device not lifted. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The state of <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse home sensor</compname><compcodenr class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr " translate="no"> 19B7 </compcodenr><compsignal class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal " translate="no">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_HOME_SE</compsignal></comp> shows that the vane of blouse forming device does not cover the sensor. Blouse forming device state is not lifted where it is expected to be lifted. Probably the sensor, the vane or the arm is broken. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Additional information (if available): 
</p><fig class="- topic/fig " id="GUID-1AB4E561-0F03-42A1-92C9-D51D65F0E7AB"><title class="- topic/title "/><image class="- topic/image " href="GUID-298FA37C-D100-4FBC-B7EA-11229CAAF84B-low.png" keyref="" placement="inline" otherprops="GUID-298FA37C-D100-4FBC-B7EA-11229CAAF84B-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> takeUpRollStatus [inserted, not inserted] 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Indicates a problem with 19S1, 19S2, 19S3. These switches are all in series.<xref class="- topic/xref " href="GUID-39282240-AADD-4642-963D-5730C98D354F.xml" type="concept"><?ditaot gentext?>19 External Output</xref>
</p><p class="- topic/p "> (0=inserted, 1=not inserted take up roll) 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> nrOfWindActionsAfterTaping [0, 1, 2, …] 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> if 19713 occurs and nrOfWindActionsAfterTaping = 1 then it can indicate that the tape became loose. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">For nrOfWindActionsAfterTaping &gt;1 the tape is probably not the cause. 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> takeUpRollOnOffSwitch [on, off] 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> indicates the status of the winder (safety switch black) when this 19713 error occurs. 
</p></li></ul></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><tsBody class="- topic/body tsTroubleshooting/tsBody "><tsSymptoms id="GUID-33E1B64A-E818-4500-A780-C8BC692D14B2" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsSymptoms "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p></tsSymptoms><tsCauses id="GUID-B6B9D0C9-67FF-4DA0-BE4E-35906A4E3CB0" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p ">Media not fixed with tape 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-1B509343-AA31-4FE2-910F-AB9D84645ED8" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / tape the media. Instruct the key operator. 
</p></tsDiagnose><tsCauses id="GUID-7109820B-BAF9-4E5F-A871-6118D12877D5" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsCauses "><p class="- topic/p "><comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse home sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_HOME_SE</compsignal></comp> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The home sensor might be broken. The home sensor is checked during initialization. In case faulty results in a clamp homing timeout. 
</p></tsCauses><tsDiagnose id="GUID-9F8EFD97-A6A5-4102-AAB2-F101E9E08926" class="- topic/section tsTroubleshooting/tsDiagnose "><p class="- topic/p ">Check / replace <comp class="+ topic/ph oce-d/comp "><compname class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compname ">External output winder blouse home sensor</compname><compcodenr translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compcodenr "> 19B7 </compcodenr><compsignal translate="no" class="+ topic/keyword oce-d/compsignal ">EXO_WND_BLOUSE_HOME_SE</compsignal></comp>. 
